## Generating Open Source Attributions for Projects using PyPI

### Using CycloneDX BOM tool
The prefered method to produce an OSPI (BOM with license information) for a PyPI project is to use the CycloneDX-BOM tool to generate a BOM, and then parse the BOM to produce a Legal Notices file.
Assuming you are working inside a Python virtual enviroment:

> pip install cyclonedx-bom
> cyclonedx-py environment --gather-license-texts --of XML > bom.xml

Once the BOM file is available, we can use a simple Python script to parse the data into an attribution notices. You can find an example <HERE>.
> python3 bom2notices.py

### Using PIP-Licenses to produce a list of packages

Another option is to use the tool pip-licenses to generate a simplified BOM (KissBOM) in CSV format, and the same approach can be used to generate a Legal Notices file:

> pip-licenses --from=mixed --with-url --format=csv > BOM.csv
> pip-licenses --from=mixed --with-url --with-license-file --with-notice-file > Notice.txt

This option is functional but more rudimentary than using CycloneDX-bom tooling.